      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The electronic controller <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">N1</b> compares the output voltage
with the adjusted set-point value. Depending on the difference between
the measured and set-point value, the motor <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">M1</b> will adjust
the variable auto transformer <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T2</b>.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The adjusted voltage
of the variable auto transformer <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T2</b> is transferred to the primary
winding of the booster transformer <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T1</b>, which is rated for the
maximum bypass mains voltage deviation. The secondary winding of the
booster transformer <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T1</b> is placed in the line branch of the
bypass mains to compensate for voltage variations. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">With the
bypass mains stabilizer <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T090</b> the actual value of the output
voltage will be observed with an accuracy of ± 1 % at a deviation
of the incoming bypass mains voltage of ±10 / ±15 / ±20
% of the set-point value (depending on type of transformer). A change
of the load has no influence on the accuracy of the output voltage.</p>
